          <msContents class="thematic">
            <summary> This manuscript contains a commentary on the book of Aphorisms
                            attributed to <persName type="standard" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/287984736" key="n 80119944 ">Hippocrates</persName>. </summary>
            <msItem>
              <author>
                <name type="person" key="n 2008049541" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/4405945" subtype="aut">
                  <persName xml:lang="eng">Ibn Abī Ṣādiq‏</persName>
                  <persName xml:lang="ara">ابن أبي صادق</persName>
                </name>
              </author>
              <title xml:lang="eng" type="desc">Commentary on Hippocratic
                                Aphorisms</title>
              <title xml:lang="ara">شرح فصول أبقراط</title>
              <title xml:lang="eng" type="alt">Sharḥ Fuṣūl Abuqrāṭ</title>
              <note> This is a thematically arranged commentary (see <ref type="article"> Pormann, Joosse
                                2012, pp. 221-222</ref>). The introduction begins on f. 1b and the table
                                of contents is in ff. 2b-3a. The beginning of each bāb is as
                                follows: Bab 1: f. 3a; Bab 2: f. 8b; Bab 3: f. 18a; Bab 4: f. 32a;
                                Bab 5: f. 37a; Bab 6: f. 46b; Bab 7: f. 90a (“On diseases afflicting
                                women”); Bab 8: f. 101b; Bab 9: f. 109b; Bab 10: f. 111a; Bab 11: f.
                                117a; Bab 12: f. 118b; Bab 13: f. 120b; Bab 14: f. 122b ("On crises
                                and their days, and the purges that happen in them and the symptoms
                                that occur during [the crisis]"); Bab 15: f. 130a; Bab 16: f. 136a;
                                Bab 17: f. 137a; Bab 18: f. 138a (On drink); Bab 19: f. 139b; Bab
                                20: f. 143b.
                                And conclusion (khātima) is on f. 148b.
                                The copy is complete.
                            </note>
